AnnotationAssertion(Annotation(<http://www.geneontology.org/formats/oboInOwl#hasDbXref> "FlyBase:FBrf0064792") <http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/IAO_0000115> <http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/FBbt_00001862> "Anterior-most part of the embryonic/larval alimentary canal. It opens anteriorly at the mouth and is composed of the atrium (to which the salivary glands are attached), the pharynx, and the esophagus and part of the proventriculus.")
