AnnotationAssertion(Annotation(<http://www.geneontology.org/formats/oboInOwl#hasDbXref> "FlyBase:FBrf0074444") Annotation(<http://www.geneontology.org/formats/oboInOwl#hasDbXref> "FlyBase:FBrf0134542") <http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/IAO_0000115> <http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/FBbt_00005062> "An immature hemocyte. It is highly basophilic, with a round to polygonal morphology and measures approximately 4 to 6 micrometers in diameter (Shrestha and Gateff, 1982). The nucleus is rich in nucleoli and is surrounded by a thin band of ribosome-rich cytoplasm (Shrestha and Gateff, 1982). In the larva, these cells can be found in the lymph gland primary lobe, or in circulation (Lanot et al., 2001).")
