# Class: <http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/FBbt_00005331> (dorsal closure embryo)

AnnotationAssertion(Annotation(<http://www.geneontology.org/formats/oboInOwl#hasDbXref> "FlyBase:FBrf0064803") Annotation(<http://www.geneontology.org/formats/oboInOwl#hasDbXref> "FlyBase:FBrf0089570") <http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/IAO_0000115> <http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/FBbt_00005331> "Embryo during the dorsal closure stage, which corresponds to stages 13-15 (Hartenstein, 1993; Campos-Ortega and Hartenstein, 1997). Dorsal closure occurs by extension of the dorsal epidermal primordium on either side, leading to fusion at the dorsal midline (Campos-Ortega and Hartenstein, 1997).")
