# Class: <http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/FBbt_00005508> (mushroom body primordium)

AnnotationAssertion(Annotation(<http://www.geneontology.org/formats/oboInOwl#hasDbXref> "FlyBase:FBrf0144836") <http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/IAO_0000115> <http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/FBbt_00005508> "Embryonic structure from which the mushroom body is derived. The development of the mushroom body proceeds as follows: axonogenesis of embryonic Kenyon cells starts late in embryonic stage 14. The axons from these cells extend towards the lateral protocerebral tract (LTP). During stage 16, a second set of Kenyon cell fibers form a second tract, closely apposed to the first. By late stage 16, both tracts extend anteriorly beyond the LTP to form the distal part of the peduncle. These tracts make a sharp medial turn close to the boundary with the deutocerebrum to form the medial lobe. By late stage 17 the vertical lobe has emerged as a collateral outgrowth from the point where these tracts bend. Finally, the calyx forms near to the end of embryogenesis.")
AnnotationAssertion(<http://www.geneontology.org/formats/oboInOwl#hasAlternativeId> <http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/FBbt_00005508> "FBbt:00005666")
AnnotationAssertion(<http://www.geneontology.org/formats/oboInOwl#hasDbXref> <http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/FBbt_00005508> "VFB:FBbt_00005508")
AnnotationAssertion(<http://www.geneontology.org/formats/oboInOwl#hasExactSynonym> <http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/FBbt_00005508> "embryonic central brain mushroom body")
AnnotationAssertion(<http://www.geneontology.org/formats/oboInOwl#hasOBONamespace> <http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/FBbt_00005508> "fly_anatomy.ontology")
AnnotationAssertion(<http://www.geneontology.org/formats/oboInOwl#id> <http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/FBbt_00005508> "FBbt:00005508")
AnnotationAssertion(<http://www.geneontology.org/formats/oboInOwl#inSubset> <http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/FBbt_00005508> <http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/fbbt#cur>)
AnnotationAssertion(rdfs:label <http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/FBbt_00005508> "mushroom body primordium")
