# Class: <http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/FBbt_00005541> (cardiogenic mesoderm)

AnnotationAssertion(Annotation(<http://www.geneontology.org/formats/oboInOwl#hasDbXref> "FlyBase:FBrf0089570") Annotation(<http://www.geneontology.org/formats/oboInOwl#hasDbXref> "FlyBase:FBrf0253577") <http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/IAO_0000115> <http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/FBbt_00005541> "Dorsal-most region of the trunk mesoderm that gives rise to the dorsal vessel (Campos-Ortega and Hartenstein, 1997). It forms a leading edge as the invaginated trunk mesoderm spreads from ventral to dorsal (Campos-Ortega and Hartenstein, 1997). The left and right regions eventually fuse at the dorsal midline and their cells differentiate into cardioblasts and pericardial cells (Campos-Ortega and Hartenstein, 1997).")
