# Class: <http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/FBbt_00005646> (embryonic precursor of adult hindgut)

AnnotationAssertion(Annotation(<http://www.geneontology.org/formats/oboInOwl#hasDbXref> "FlyBase:FBrf0064792") <http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/IAO_0000115> <http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/FBbt_00005646> "Imaginal cell, set aside during embryonic development, that will give rise to the adult hindgut. These cells are found in two rings of the hindgut; immediately posterior to the ureters of the Malpighian tubules, and at the anus. These two rings grow out and eventually unite.")
