# Class: <http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/FBbt_00051393> (adult sensory region of subesophageal zone)

AnnotationAssertion(Annotation(<http://www.geneontology.org/formats/oboInOwl#hasDbXref> "FlyBase:FBrf0211916") Annotation(<http://www.geneontology.org/formats/oboInOwl#hasDbXref> "FlyBase:FBrf0237251") Annotation(<http://www.geneontology.org/formats/oboInOwl#hasDbXref> "FlyBase:FBrf0254134") <http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/IAO_0000115> <http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/FBbt_00051393> "Synaptic neuropil subdomain of the adult subesophageal zone that houses the axon terminals of sensory neurons (Miyazaki and Ito, 2010; Kendroud et al., 2018). Larger domains can be defined based on the projection patterns of neurons entering the brain via particular roots of the maxillary-labial, pharyngeal and antennal nerves (Kendroud et al., 2018). Many smaller domains, usually subdomains of the larger regions, can also be defined based on neuron morphology and function (Miyazaki and Ito, 2010; Munch et al., 2022).")
