# Class: <http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/FBbt_00100532> (type I neuroblast)

AnnotationAssertion(Annotation(<http://www.geneontology.org/formats/oboInOwl#hasDbXref> "FlyBase:FBrf0207387") Annotation(<http://www.geneontology.org/formats/oboInOwl#hasDbXref> "FlyBase:FBrf0225698") <http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/IAO_0000115> <http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/FBbt_00100532> "Neuroblast that divides asymmetrically to regenerate itself and produce a smaller ganglion mother cell that generates two daughter neurons. Many of these neuroblasts switch to type 0 division at some point during their development, to produce daughters that develop into neurons with no further division (Baumgardt et al., 2014).")
AnnotationAssertion(<http://purl.org/dc/terms/contributor> <http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/FBbt_00100532> <https://www.researchgate.net/scientific-contributions/Simon-Reeve-2162827703>)
