# Class: <http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/FBbt_00111738> (optic lobe neuroepithelial cell)

AnnotationAssertion(Annotation(<http://www.geneontology.org/formats/oboInOwl#hasDbXref> "FlyBase:FBrf0193624") Annotation(<http://www.geneontology.org/formats/oboInOwl#hasDbXref> "FlyBase:FBrf0204205") Annotation(<http://www.geneontology.org/formats/oboInOwl#hasDbXref> "FlyBase:FBrf0240123") <http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/IAO_0000115> <http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/FBbt_00111738> "Symmetrically-dividing stem cell with epithelial properties and a columnar morphology that is a precursor to an optic neuroblast (Egger et al., 2007). These cells increase in number by symmetric divisions during embryonic and larval development (Egger et al., 2007). A small number differentiate into optic neuroblasts during the embryonic stage, while the remainder enter G0 quiescence prior to larval hatching (Hakes et al., 2018). Divisions resume in the first instar (Hakes et al., 2018), followed by differentiation to neuroblasts mainly during the third instar stage (Yasugi et al., 2008).")
